# project.md — Project-Specific Standards

> **Status: optional.** This file is for conventions specific to this
> project. Leave it empty if the project has no conventions beyond what
> CLAUDE-base.md and user.md provide.
>
> **Location:** This file lives in the project repository at
> `standards/project.md`, not in the Livery submodule. It is
> project-owned, not methodology-owned.
>
> **Precedence:** Project standards win over all other standards files
> (user.md, language-rust.md, ousterhout.md, arc.md). They are the
> most specific layer.

---

## How to Use This File

Add project conventions as sections below. Examples:

- "This project uses `ureq` 2.x for HTTP; do not introduce `reqwest`"
- "All date strings are ISO 8601; never use locale-dependent formatting"
- "The `publish` crate is the only crate with network access"
- "Test fixtures are generated by helper functions, not committed as files"
- "JSON output uses camelCase keys to match the upstream API"
- "Error messages must include the file path that caused the error"

This file is also the right place for conventions that emerged during
development and were recorded in SESSIONS.md as decisions — promoting
them here ensures future sessions follow the same convention without
re-reading the full session history.

